Israeli authorities are concerned about militants entering through the porous border with Egypt's Sinai peninsula.
A suicide bombing in Dimona killed one woman and wounded 11, near a top-secret nuclear reactor.
The attack, the first since peace talks resumed, followed a breach between Egypt and Gaza.
The Al Aqsa Martyrs Brigades claimed responsibility, working with other groups.
Confusion arose over the bombers' origin, with Hamas denying involvement.
Security forces fear further infiltration from Gaza.
The incident highlights the ongoing struggle against terrorism in southern Israel, with calls for peace negotiations to continue despite the violence.
